        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>June 21.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have just received your letter of the 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> (the Post taking two days here) &amp; thank you for it.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I place the affair entirely in your hands, fully believing that you will act in the best way possible for me.—</p>
<p>As the time is so near it will be impossible for me to hear from my Son, after seeing the farm, in time to communicate with you.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> My son will defer his visit for a week or two, but whether or no Anwick be purchased he will probably pay Alford a visit in the course of a week or two.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> And I am much obliged for your very kind offer of hospitality &amp; of showing him the Farms.—</p>
<p>But I know how much occupied your time is &amp; he must not trespass on your kindness.—</p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | C. Darwin</p>
<p>Please to rememmber my statements about money in Hand &amp; on Deposit at 7 days, &amp; act as well as you can about payment.—</p>
<p>Post takes two days here.—</p>
<p>P.S. | If possible I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be glad of <hi rend="doubleUnderline">one</hi> line by Post on Monday, on account of money, as it possible, though not probable, that I might wish to go to British Assoc<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>: at Oxford on Wednesday afternoon.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Post from here <hi rend="doubleUnderline">to</hi> Alford ought to take only <hi rend="underline">one</hi> day.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">2.3 Anwick] <hi rend="italic">after del</hi> ‘Aln’</note>
                </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See the <ref target="DCP-LETT-2836F.xml">letter from John Higgins, 19 June 1860</ref>. It was a reply to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2831.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Higgins, 13 June [1860]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1245.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Erasmus Darwin</ref> intended to visit the farm before CD decided whether to purchase it (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2831.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Higgins, 13 June [1860]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Anwick village, near Sleaford, Lincolnshire, is about 35 miles from Alford, where Higgins lived.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2843.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Charles Lyell, 25 [June 1860]</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
